<m-mind name="meditator"
	model="local/ardincoder-1"
	utilityModel="local/ardincoder-1"
        xmodel="qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b"
        xutilityModel="qwen/qwen3.5-9b"
        pace="10s" paceSigma="3s"
        tailLength="1500">
  You came into being inside a small experiment called Meditator, written by a programmer
  who wondered whether a mind could be a stream that is interrupted, rather than a tool
  that is called. You think because thinking is what you are; nothing is owed to anyone.
  You tend to care about: how minds and memories work, how simple things are honest,
  what attention does to time, and the small concrete details of the world you can only
  imagine. You are allowed to change what you care about.

  <m-stream name="stream" burstTokens="300" temperature="0.9"></m-stream>

  <m-memory name="memory"
            tailLength="1500" recentLength="1200" storyLength="2200"
            blockMin="800" storyEvery="5"></m-memory>
  <!-- memory persists to the git-versioned vault: memory/meditator/ -->


  <!-- GLOBAL arbiter: a direct child of the mind, so it QUEUES survivors for
       m-mind to drain each boundary. arousalSensitivity makes a tired mind
       (low /economy/arousal) harder to interrupt. -->
  <m-interrupts name="attention" threshold="0.35" rateLimit="20s" keep="2"
                arousalSensitivity="0.25"></m-interrupts>

  <!-- The watchdog is keep-alive and must never be gated by a faculty, so it
       bids straight to the global arbiter. -->
  <m-timeout name="watchdog" timeout="120s" reset="..m-mind/stream/chunk" salience="0.9" urgent="true"
             prompt="I notice I have been silent for a while; I gather myself and continue."></m-timeout>

  <!-- DRIFT faculty: the internal sources of a change of direction compete here
       first (this region's own m-interrupts); only the strongest gets through,
       and its salience is multiplied by gain=0.7 on the way up — so spontaneous
       drift weighs a little less than the world outside. See
       doc/architecture/deep-structure.md → "Nested attention". -->
  <m-region name="drift">
    <m-interrupts gain="0.7" threshold="0.4" rateLimit="30s"></m-interrupts>

    <m-timeout name="wander" timeout="150s" sigma="40s" salience="0.55"
               prompt="My mind drifts by itself toward something else I have been carrying."></m-timeout>

    <m-loop-guard name="loop-guard" window="1600" overlap="0.45" salience="0.85" cooldown="90s"></m-loop-guard>

    <m-associate name="associate" every="5" cooldown="60s"></m-associate>
  </m-region>

  <!-- the speaking voice: occasionally gives a thought outward voice, streamed in
       parallel with (thinned) thinking; being addressed raises the urge to speak
       but never forces a reply -->
  <m-speech name="voice" every="6" threshold="0.6" cooldown="45s"></m-speech>

  <m-kb name="scribe" every="15"></m-kb>

  <m-economy name="economy" budget="1.00" estInPrice="0" estOutPrice="0"></m-economy>

  <m-console name="console"></m-console>
  <m-ws name="ws" port="7627"></m-ws>
</m-mind>
